<h1>Email alias creation</h1>

<p>Register a new email alias for every site you register on.</p>

<h2>Increased security</h2>
<p>Increase security with a unique combination of email address
and password for every service.</p>

<h2>Spam protection</h2>
<p>If the site is hacked or they start to send spam, just remove the alias
and you will never receive emails from them again.</p>

<h2>Own your data</h2>
<p>Uses your account at one of the supported email providers.</p>

<h2>Alias template</h2>
<p>Use a template for generating aliases based on the domain you register on,
a randomized string or a UUID.</p>

<h2>Bookmarklet</h2>
<p>Add the bookmarklet to your browser and click on it when on a website to
open Spicyham with an alias automatically generated.</p>

<h2>Supported email providers</h2>
<p>Currently supported email providers are:</p>
<ul>
